# RustyHand Environment Variables (v0.7.x)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in only what you actually use.
# All lines are commented by default — uncomment the ones you need.
#
# Docker: the entrypoint auto-generates ~/.rustyhand/config.toml from
# these RUSTYHAND_* vars on first boot. Set RUSTYHAND_FORCE_ENV_CONFIG=1
# to regenerate on every boot (overrides a mounted config.toml).
#
# Binary install: these vars are read at runtime too. Channel and API
# key vars (TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, ...) are also
# referenced by name from config.toml via `*_env` fields.
#
# Pre-v0.7.5 the entrypoint wrote bare `[telegram]` / `[discord]` /
# `[slack]` sections that the daemon silently ignored — channels
# appeared as "Not configured" and inbound listeners never started.
# Fixed in v0.7.5: the entrypoint now writes `[channels.*]` subtables.
# If you upgraded an existing volume, set RUSTYHAND_FORCE_ENV_CONFIG=1
# once to regenerate config.toml in the new format.
#
# v0.7.5 also drops 35 little-used channel adapters (Matrix/WhatsApp/
# Signal/Teams/IRC/...). Only Telegram, Discord, and Slack ship now —
# they all work without a public webhook URL, so they actually run in
# a typical localhost / home Docker setup. To bring back a removed
# adapter, restore from a v0.7.4 checkout.
#
# v0.7.10 fixed the bundled agent manifests to use supported providers
# (anthropic / minimax / deepseek), so a fresh install with
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set spawns and replies on the first message — no
# `rustyhand init` step required. If you previously ran `init` and
# have a stale `~/.rustyhand/agents/<name>/agent.toml` referencing a
# removed provider (groq, gemini, openai), the v0.7.11+ resolver
# logs a warning and falls through to the image-bundled copy
# automatically. To force a clean refresh on a Docker volume, delete
# `/data/agents/` and restart.

# ─── LLM Provider API Keys ───────────────────────────────────────────
# v0.7.0 shipped a lean catalog — set ONE of these and RustyHand
# auto-detects the provider on boot. Priority: anthropic → kimi →
# deepseek → zhipu → minimax → openrouter.

# Anthropic (default) — Claude Opus / Sonnet / Haiku
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Kimi Code (Moonshot) — Anthropic-compatible, 256K context
# KIMI_API_KEY=sk-...

# DeepSeek V4 Flash / V4 Pro (V3/R1 legacy, deprecated 2026-07-24)
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...

# Zhipu GLM-4.6
# ZHIPU_API_KEY=...

# MiniMax M1 / M2.7 (1M context)
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=eyJ...

# OpenRouter — universal gateway to any upstream model via one key
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# Ollama — local, no key needed. Default http://localhost:11434/v1.
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=ignored     # set a value if your proxy needs one

# ─── Embedding-only upstreams ────────────────────────────────────────
# Independent of the LLM provider. Used for semantic memory recall.

# Voyage AI (voyage-3, voyage-code-3, voyage-multilingual-2, ...)
# VOYAGE_API_KEY=pa-...

# OpenAI text-embedding-3-* — embedding-only (OpenAI is NOT an LLM
# provider in v0.7.x; use openrouter + openai/gpt-* for completion).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ─── Channel tokens ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Telegram bot — obtain from @BotFather on Telegram.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABC-DEF...

# Restrict the bot to specific Telegram user IDs (highly recommended —
# unrestricted bots can drain your LLM budget within minutes). Accepts
# a comma-separated list; brackets and quotes are tolerated. Channel
# IDs are negative integers.
#   Example: single user
#     RUSTYHAND_TELEGRAM_USERS=123456789
#   Example: multiple users + a channel
#     RUSTYHAND_TELEGRAM_USERS=123456789, 987654321, -1001234567890
#   Example: bracket syntax also accepted
#     RUSTYHAND_TELEGRAM_USERS=[123456789,987654321]
# Non-integer tokens are dropped with a warning at boot — a typo here
# will not crash the daemon. Leaving this unset (or all-invalid) makes
# the bot accept messages from ANY Telegram user.
# RUSTYHAND_TELEGRAM_USERS=

# Discord bot
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...

# Slack bot — set SLACK_APP_TOKEN too for Socket Mode.
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...

# ─── Default agent per channel ───────────────────────────────────────
# Since v0.7.7 the docker entrypoint defaults `default_agent = "assistant"`
# under each `[channels.*]` section it generates — a fresh container
# routes messages straight to the bundled `assistant` agent without
# manual config edits.
#
# Override per channel by setting these env vars to a different agent
# name. Set to an empty string to skip the default_agent line entirely
# and rely on bindings / direct routes instead.
#
# Even without these set, the v0.7.10+ channel bridge has a runtime
# fallback chain: if the router can't resolve a target, it routes to
# the first running agent (alphabetical) or attempts to spawn one of
# the bundled meta-agents (assistant → coordinator → coder). A user
# only sees the "set default_agent in config.toml" error message when
# every fallback fails.
# RUSTYHAND_TELEGRAM_DEFAULT_AGENT=assistant
# RUSTYHAND_DISCORD_DEFAULT_AGENT=assistant
# RUSTYHAND_SLACK_DEFAULT_AGENT=assistant

# ─── RustyHand daemon ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Bearer token required on every /api/* request (leave unset for
# trusted-localhost access only).
# RUSTYHAND_API_KEY=

# HTTP bind address. Docker defaults to 0.0.0.0:4200.
# RUSTYHAND_API_LISTEN=127.0.0.1:4200

# Default provider + model (auto-detected if unset). These populate
# [default_model] in the generated config.toml.
# RUSTYHAND_PROVIDER=anthropic
# RUSTYHAND_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514
# RUSTYHAND_MODEL_KEY_ENV=ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# RUSTYHAND_MODEL_BASE_URL=                # optional endpoint override

# Fallback chain — used when the primary LLM fails (rate-limit, auth).
# RUSTYHAND_FALLBACK_PROVIDER=openrouter
# RUSTYHAND_FALLBACK_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4
# RUSTYHAND_FALLBACK_KEY_ENV=OPENROUTER_API_KEY

# Spend limits in USD (0 = unlimited). Enforced per-agent AND globally.
# RUSTYHAND_BUDGET_HOURLY=0.50
# RUSTYHAND_BUDGET_DAILY=5.00
# RUSTYHAND_BUDGET_MONTHLY=50.00

# Shell exec policy for agents: deny | allowlist | full.
# RUSTYHAND_EXEC_MODE=allowlist

# Agent-to-Agent protocol on/off.
# RUSTYHAND_A2A_ENABLED=false

# Per-response usage footer: Off | Tokens | Cost | Full.
# RUSTYHAND_USAGE_FOOTER=Full

# Memory decay + embedding provider (see `rustyhand models providers`).
# Setting an embedding provider is OPTIONAL — without one, the daemon
# falls back to text search (SQLite LIKE). When the embedding endpoint
# is unreachable the v0.7.11+ driver short-circuits subsequent calls
# for 30s instead of spamming `error sending request` warnings on
# every message; recovery is logged once at INFO level.
# RUSTYHAND_MEMORY_DECAY=0.05
# RUSTYHAND_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=voyage      # voyage | openai | ollama
# RUSTYHAND_EMBEDDING_KEY_ENV=VOYAGE_API_KEY

# Force the Docker entrypoint to regenerate config.toml from env on
# every boot, overriding any persisted file. Useful when updating the
# container image — without this, env changes are ignored if a
# config.toml already exists in the volume.
# RUSTYHAND_FORCE_ENV_CONFIG=1

# Log level: trace | debug | info | warn | error.
# RUST_LOG=info
# RUST_LOG=rusty_hand=debug                # debug RustyHand only
